6\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jfg1705567612144.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jfg1705567612144.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jfg1705567612144.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ury1665702778507\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                             \n Creating Global ProcScripts\n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Global ProcScript modules are defined and deployed in Global ProcScript libraries.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"ury1665702778507__context_w3808ab1b5b1_w3809ab1b5_w3810ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"ury1665702778507__topic_d12923e1_d12924e1_d12925e1\">You must have created a project to contain your\n\t\tapplication definitions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>.\n                             </div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ury1665702778507__li_d6116e1_d6117e1_d6118e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Open your project. In the U-Bar, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Browse</span>, select\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">prj</code>, then choose the project you want to open.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ury1665702778507__li_d6122e1_d6123e1_d6124e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you have not already done so, create a Global ProcScript Library:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"ury1665702778507__li_d6125e1_d6126e1_d6127e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Templates</span> tab of the Resource Browser, select the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Global ProcScript Library</code> template.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Drag and drop it onto the project in the Structure Editor.</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Rename the library.</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally, edit the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Description</span> property to provide a\n                     more informative description.</span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ury1665702778507__li_d6137e1_d6138e1_d6139e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ury1665702778507__p_d12938e1_d12939e1_d12940e1\">Double-click the Library to open it, or\n               right-click it and choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Open</span> from the menu.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"ury1665702778507__fig_w3811ab1b5b3b5b3b1b1_w3812ab1b5b3b5b3b1_w3813ab1b5b3b5b3_w3814ab1b5b3b5_w3815ab1b5b3_w3816ab1b5_w3817ab1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Global ProcScript Library Editor: Define Structure Worksheet</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Global ProcScript Library Editor: Define Structure Worksheet\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/libprc_definestructure_ws.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 1. Global ProcScript Library Editor: Define Structure Worksheet\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/libprc_definestructure_ws.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ury1665702778507__li_d6140e1_d6141e1_d6142e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ury1665702778507__p_d12941e1_d12942e1_d12943e1\">Drag and drop a template from the Resource\n               Browser onto the Library object in the Structure pane.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Uniface provides a default template called <code class=\"ph codeph\">Empty ProcScript</code>in the\n               UPALETTE_LIBPRC palette.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ury1665702778507__li_d6143e1_d6144e1_d6145e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Rename the Global ProcScript object and edit the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Description</span> property to provide more information about the Global ProcScript.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ury1665702778507__li_d6146e1_d6147e1_d6148e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Go to the Write Script worksheet, select the Global ProcScript object, and edit its\n               contents. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"ury1665702778507__fig_kkd_xzh_d1c\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Global ProcScript Library Editor: Write Script Worksheet </figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Global ProcScript Library Editor: Write Script Worksheet\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/libprc_writescript_ws.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 2. Global ProcScript Library Editor: Write Script Worksheet \" id=\"ury1665702778507__image_fg2_wzh_d1c\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/libprc_writescript_ws.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ury1665702778507__p_d12944e1_d12945e1_d12946e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kvf1665702667063.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvf1665702667063.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to script application behavior using ProcScript, Uniface's own scripting language, and JavaScript, the most widely-used scripting language for web applications.\">Scripting Application Behavior</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ury1665702778507__li_d6149e1_d6150e1_d6151e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span> to compile the library and its contents.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ury1665702778507__li_d6152e1_d6153e1_d6154e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To call a global ProcScript from a component, use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">call</span> command. For example:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">call MYPRCS::Multiply(par1, par2)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cvq1665702579531.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Global ProcScripts</a><p>Global ProcScripts are global objects that are located in a runtime library and can be called from any ProcScript in the application. They enable you to define common functionality for use by one or more applications.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bka1665702579213.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>call</a><p>Execute the specified function or global ProcScript.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828946\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5828946\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Creating Global ProcScripts Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Creating Global ProcScripts Global ProcScript modules are defined and deployed in Global ProcScript libraries. You must have created a project to contain your application definitions. For more information, see Working with Projects . Open your project. In the U-Bar, click Browse , select prj , then choose the project you want to open. If you have not already done so, create a Global ProcScript Library: In the Templates tab of the Resource Browser, select the Global ProcScript Library template. Drag and drop it onto the project in the Structure Editor. Rename the library. Optionally, edit the Description property to provide a more informative description. Double-click the Library to open it, or right-click it and choose Open from the menu. Figure 1. Global ProcScript Library Editor: Define Structure Worksheet Drag and drop a template from the Resource Browser onto the Library object in the Structure pane. Uniface provides a default template called Empty ProcScript in the UPALETTE_LIBPRC palette. Rename the Global ProcScript object and edit the Description property to provide more information about the Global ProcScript. Go to the Write Script worksheet, select the Global ProcScript object, and edit its contents. Figure 2. Global ProcScript Library Editor: Write Script Worksheet For more information, see Scripting Application Behavior . Click Compile to compile the library and its contents. To call a global ProcScript from a component, use the call command. For example: call MYPRCS::Multiply(par1, par2) Copy Related Links Global ProcScripts Global ProcScripts are global objects that are located in a runtime library and can be called from any ProcScript in the application. They enable you to define common functionality for use by one or more applications. call Execute the specified function or global ProcScript. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}